Class StudentCardResponse

java.lang.Object
com.example.cab302tailproject.model.StudentCardResponse
public class StudentCardResponse extends Object
Represents a student's response to a learning card. This class is used to model data from the 'StudentCardResponse' database table.

  • Constructor Details

    • StudentCardResponse

      public StudentCardResponse(int responseID, int studentID, int materialID, String cardQuestion, boolean isCorrect, int classroomID)
      Constructor for creating a StudentCardResponse object.
      Parameters:
      responseID - The unique ID of the response (usually auto-generated by the database).
      studentID - The ID of the student who made the response.
      materialID - The ID of the learning card material/deck.
      cardQuestion - The text of the question on the card.
      isCorrect - True if the student's answer was correct, false otherwise.
      classroomID - The ID of the classroom the student was in when responding.
